  "description": "Growing protocol for *Atriplex hortensis*, heat- and drought-tolerant annual producing dramatic deep-purple foliage. Tall plant (4–6 feet); grown for ornamental-edible dual-use. Rapid development (40–50 days to mature), early bolting but short-season crop allows succession plantings. Excellent summer alternative to heat-sensitive spinach and lettuce.",
